            <head xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-Hd1e108">Rubrica 4</head>
            <head xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-Hd1e111" type="question-title">De arrogantia: insolentia: iactantia et vanagloria</head>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-d1e114">
              De arrogantia iactantia insolentia
              et uanagloria
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-d1e121">
              <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-Rd1e118">Salo<lb ed="#C" break="no"/>mon 
              <lb ed="#C"/>in prouerbiis capitulo 16</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-Qd1e127">Abhominatio domini est omnis 
              arrogans.</quote> 
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-d1e135"> 
              ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-Rd1e133">Idem 24 capitulo</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-Qd1e137">Qui se iac<lb ed="#C" break="no"/>tat 
              et dilatat iurgia concitatur</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-d1e144"> 
              ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-Rd1e144">Idem in
              <lb ed="#C"/>ecclesiastes capitulo 7</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-Qd1e146">Melior est in patiens arrogante</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-d1e152">
              <lb ed="#C"/>¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-Rd1e156">Aristoteles magnorum moralium libro I capitulo LII</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-Qd1e156">Iacta<lb ed="#C" break="no"/>tior 
              est plus eis qui sunt sibi fingens esse
              <lb ed="#C"/>aut scire que non sciuit</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-d1e164">
              ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-Rd1e170">Oratius in poetria</ref>
              <lb ed="#C"/><quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-Qd1e168">parturies montes nascetur ridiculus
              <lb ed="#C"/>mus</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-d1e174">
              ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-Rd1e182">Tullius rethoricorum artis ueteris libro I capitulo 12</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-Qd1e178">Ex
              <lb ed="#C"/>Ex arrogantia odium solet euenire ex
              <lb ed="#C"/>insolentia arrogantia</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-d1e186">
              ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-Rd1e196">Quintillianus 8
              <cb ed="#C" n="b"/>
              <lb ed="#C"/>declamatione</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-Qd1e190">Insolentiam immeritam quam poten<lb ed="#C" break="no"/>tiam 
              carpit</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-d1e202"> 
              ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-Rd1e213">Idem 17 et finali declamatus</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-Qd1e204">Pars uol<lb ed="#C" break="no"/>uptatis 
              uidetur esse iactatio</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-d1e211">
              ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-Rd1e226">Seneca epistolarum
              <lb ed="#C"/>ad lucillum epistolarum libro 12 epistola II et finali</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-Qd1e215">Diuitie inso<lb ed="#C" break="no"/>lentiam 
              dant nichil aliud est insolentia quam
              <lb ed="#C"/>spes flere magnitudinis</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-d1e223">
              ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-Rd1e241">Idem de remediis
              <lb ed="#C"/>fortuitorum capitulo 21 et finali</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-Qd1e227">Facilius reges animum
              <lb ed="#C"/>nulla uanitate rerum tumentium</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-d1e235">
              <lb ed="#C"/>¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-Rd1e256">Auctor libelli de formulae honeste uite capitulo II</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-Qd1e239">Non eris arro<lb ed="#C" break="no"/>gans 
              que nosti sine arrogantia postulanti
              <lb ed="#C"/>im parties</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-d1e247">
              ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-Rd1e273">boetius in topicis libro III</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-Qd1e251">Ex arrogan<lb ed="#C" break="no"/>tia 
              quisque odiosus</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-d1e257">
              ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-Rd1e285">ysidorus soliloquiorum
              <lb ed="#C"/>libro II capitulo XIII</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-Qd1e261">Caue inanis glorie studium
              <lb ed="#C"/>non arroges non te iactes non te insolenter
              <lb ed="#C"/>extollas</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-d1e269"> 
              ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-Rd1e297">Idem 28</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-Qd1e271">Magnus numquam ui<lb ed="#C" break="no"/>deri 
              studeas</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-d1e278"> 
              ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-Rd1e308">Idem 44 capitulo</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-Qd1e280">Superiori equa<lb ed="#C" break="no"/>le 
              summa</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-d1e286">
              ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-Rd1e320">Bernardus libro de improbatione uitiorum capitulo II</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-Qd1e290">Vana super<lb ed="#C" break="no"/>borum 
              uacuat iactatio meniem</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-d1e296">
              ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-Rd1e333">Gaulfredus
              <lb ed="#C"/>in poetria capitulo 31</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-Qd1e300">Cum fueris maior aliis te fin<lb ed="#C" break="no"/>ge 
              minorem Et te mentire tibi nec sic in abis<lb ed="#C" break="no"/>sum 
              deitias alios ut te super ethera tollas
              <lb ed="#C"/>Vincat opus uerbum minuit iactantia fa<lb ed="#C" break="no"/>mem</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-d1e312">
              ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-Rd1e351">Idem capitulo 20</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-Qd1e316">Vtere consilio licet
              <lb ed="#C"/>omnia noueris vnus Maior in hoc aliis in uere<lb ed="#C" break="no"/>beris 
              si tamen vnus Ex aliis nec sis elati
              <lb ed="#C"/>sed socialis Eloquii ueterum clamat doctri<lb ed="#C" break="no"/>na 
              loquaris ut plures sapias ut pau<lb ed="#C" break="no"/>ci</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-d1e330">
              ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-Rd1e371">Yesus filius sirach in ecclesiastco XXXII</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-Qd1e334">In multis esto
              <lb ed="#C"/>quasi iustus et audi tactus et similes que<lb ed="#C" break="no"/>rens </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-d1e342">
              ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-Rd1e385">Ouidius de tristibus libro I epistola I</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-Qd1e346">Dum
              <lb ed="#C"/>poterit infirmus nimium sublimia penis yca<lb ed="#C" break="no"/>rus 
              equoreas nomine fecit aquis</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-d1e365"> 
              ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-Rd1e415">Valerius
              <lb ed="#C"/>maximus libro III titulo de fiducia</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-Qd1e369">Laudata pro<lb ed="#C" break="no"/>fecto 
              fiducia est que estimationem sui cer<lb ed="#C" break="no"/>to 
              pondere distans examinat Tantum sibi
              <lb ed="#C"/>arrogans quantum a contemptum et insolentia sa<lb ed="#C" break="no"/>tis 
              distare est</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-d1e355">
              ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-Rd1e403">Seneca de natura libro I</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-Qd1e359">In rui<pb ed="#C" n="108-v"/><cb ed="#C" n="a"/><lb ed="#C" break="no"/>nam \
              prona sunt que sine fundamentis creuere</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-d1e388">
              <lb ed="#C"/><ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-Rd1e439">Marcialis cocus libro vndique suscepto. capitulo II</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-Qd1e392">Sepe ruis dum<lb ed="#C" break="no"/>sepe 
              petis atque in cautus quam ruina sepe sit
              <lb ed="#C"/>sufficiens una ruina tibi</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-d1e400"> 
              ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-Rd1e452">Idem capitulo
              <lb ed="#C"/>4</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-Qd1e402">Altior ascensus grauior plerumque ruina
              <lb ed="#C"/>est Solicitudo grauis est paratus honor Cum
              <lb ed="#C"/>nimis alta petis atque incautusque ruina
              <lb ed="#C"/>Est grauis et subita sexte timende tibi</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-d1e414">
              <lb ed="#C"/><ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-Rd1e470">Uegetius
              <lb ed="#C"/>de re militari
              <lb ed="#C"/>libro III capitulo V</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-Qd1e418">Interdum imperita rusticitas plu<lb ed="#C" break="no"/>ra 
              promittit et credit se scire que nesciat</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-d1e426">
              <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-Rd1e484">Aucto
              <lb ed="#C"/>libro de formula honeste uite capitulo II</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-Qd1e430">Non altiori rei te im<lb ed="#C" break="no"/>ponas 
              in qua statim tibi ascendenti tremendus
              <lb ed="#C"/>descendendi caudus est</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-d1e439">
              ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-Rd1e499">Cassiodorus epistolarum libro V epistola
              <lb ed="#C"/>XIII</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-Qd1e443">Ignorat modum seruare presumptio nec
              <lb ed="#C"/>post sub modo redigi cum licentia affuerit ui<lb ed="#C" break="no"/>sa 
              concedi</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-d1e451">
              ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-Rd1e513">Versificator fabularum ysopi fabula 36</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-Qd1e455">qui plus
              <lb ed="#C"/>posse putat sua quam natura ministrat posse suum
              <lb ed="#C"/>superans se minus ipse potest</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-d1e463">
              ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-Rd1e527">Baldo fabula 30</ref>
              <lb ed="#C"/><quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-Qd1e467">Non multas uires discant presumere uiles</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-d1e473">
              <lb ed="#C"/>¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-Rd1e539">Mattheus vindocinensis in poetria libro I capitulo 6</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-Qd1e477">In<lb ed="#C" break="no"/>consulta 
              nocet presumptio fallitur errat
              <lb ed="#C"/>naturale putans dilapidare bonum</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-d1e485">
              ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-Rd1e553">Gaulfredus
              <lb ed="#C"/>in poetria capitulo 31</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-Qd1e489">Et uires metire tuas si forte
              <lb ed="#C"/>es aude Grandia si fragilis humeris inpone
              <lb ed="#C"/>minora Si mediocris ama mediocria su<lb ed="#C" break="no"/>mere 
              noli que quando sumis presumas</quote>
            </p>
            <p>
              ¶ Oratius
              <lb ed="#C"/>in poetria sumerite miseram uiri qui scibitis
              <lb ed="#C"/>equam viribus et versate diu quod ferre
              <lb ed="#C"/>recuset quid ualeat humeri
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-d1e501">
              [omitted]
            </p>
         </div>
